-- Syrian Rebels Kill Three Soldiers in Daraa and Hama, SANA Says
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-04-23T12:41:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/syrian-rebels-kill-three-soldiers-in-daraa-and-hama-sana-says.html
Syrian rebels killed three
soldiers, including two officers, in Daraa and Hama, the
official  Syrian Arab News Agency  reported.  Lieutenant Colonel Said Assi was killed in a village in
Daraa province while returning home from duty in his military
unit, the news service said. Gunmen killed Colonel Mahmoud
Zaitoun and Warrant Officer Jihad Tawfik Ismael while they were
on their way to work in Hama, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
